      "file_path": "packages/apex-pdp-package-full/src/main/package/scripts/apexApps.sh",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 146,
      "message": "Maybe rather than going with this file approach, it might be better (and possibly more secure) just to hard code a function for each application, certainly I think that woul be easier to follow for maintenance of this script.\n\nSomething like below\n\nI know this is a big change to the script so I can help if you wish.\n    \n\nengine() {​​​​​​​\n    case \"$1\" in\n        -h | --help) $1Help ; exit 0 ;;\n        ...\n    esac\n}​​​​​​​\n\n\nengineHelp() {​​​​​​​\n    printf \"help for engine\"\n}​​​​​​​\n\n\n\ngui() {​​​​​​​\n    bla foo\n}​​​​​​​\n\n\nguiHelp() {​​​​​​​\n\n\n}​​​​​​​\n\n\n\ncase \"$1\" in\n    engine) engine $* ;;\n    gui)    gui $** ;;\n    *)      printf \"error %s\" \"$1\"\nesac",
